# tmux visual selection mode


+tmux +shell +visual


/Users/michal/Documents/journal/zettel/20210804124544-tmux-move-panes
/Users/michal/Documents/journal/zettel/20210804122432-nested-tmux-session


In order to do that, use the usual `C-a [`, or whatever it is mapped to in your
config, but instead of hitting space right away, press `C-v` and then space.
This will let you select text like in Vim visual mode with hjkl.
